parameters: AlainFace
\n<Alain>This is such a fluffy tail. Not as well
treated as that fox beastkin, but it's
still maintained pretty well.
Demon_Happy
\nr<Est>I've got to agree that this fur feels pretty nice.
I'm letting my actual body experience the full feedback
from this dummy, and it's so soft and silky.
Demon_Default
\nr<Est>That being said: why are we investigating here?
AlainFace
\n<Alain>I thought that if she had some magic
tool to control the traps in this dungeon,
she could have hid it in here. I guess I
was wrong.
\v[18]/7 notes made on Wolf Beastkin.
A
\n<Wolf Beastkin>Grrr... When is she going to make her move? I'm
ready for her whenever she gets close...
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Good. She hasn't realized that I'm here.
She's still keeping an eye on Gale.
Demon_Angry
\nr<Est>That's a good thing. Let her stay distracted. Come
on. There's no magic tool here. I'm leaving you behind
if you stay around here any longer.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>I'll be right there.
(It's a habit, but even with her around,
I still want to investigate my way.)
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Her toes are wriggling a bunch. It's crazy
how she's not tense at all. Is all of this
fun for her?
AlainFace
\n<Alain>But now that I'm thinking about it, she
was kicking like crazy in her fight with
Gale earlier. Could her feet have gotten
a little worn out?
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Maybe I can stab her hard enough for
her to lower her guard enough for Gale.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Huh?
Demon_Shocked
\nr<Est>Gah! You idiot! That's why I told you not to
stick around there!
Blackout
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Grhrk! Mgff!
(Her toes scrunched up all of a sudden?)
Rhea_SmugPNG
\nr<Wolf Beastkin>Heh. I thought I felt something lingering
around my toes for too long. I almost thought you were
a pebble for a second.
\nr<Wolf Beastkin>Did you think you wouldn't get caught? Let
me take care of you real quick before I deal with
your partner.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Mgghh?
(What?)
RheaToes
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Mgrhff! Mffffgff!
(Blasted! She's got my head between her
toes! I can't break free!)
\n<Wolf Beastkin>Heh. You sure are struggling there. That squirming's
a lot more entertaining than I thought.
\n<Wolf Beastkin>You're a perfect fit between my toes to the point
where it's kind of pleasant. You make a good a toe
divider.
\n<Wolf Beastkin>Maybe I'll keep you around after I take care of
your friend. Surely the Boss won't mind if I keep a
Mini adventurer as a pet.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Mggggffff! Mgggghhh!
(Toe divider? Pet? She's crazy! But this
isn't good. I can't fight back against this
vice grip her toes have on me.)
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Mgggkkk...
(The sweat and stench... I can't breathe...
My consciousness is... fading...)
Having ignored Est's warnings, Dragon Rider Alain
lingered for too long on the wolf beastkin's foot. He
was caught while investigating her soles.
In an instant, he was lifted off the floor and seized
by the titanic wolf fighter's powerful toes, still
hot and sweat from her previous battle.
Unable to breathe with his head pinched between her
toes, he knew nothing more as the wolf woman prepared
to fight Gale. Est could not help, meaning his chance
to escaping his fate as a toe divider was next to none.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Wow. This wolf woman has to be martial
artist to have such toned legs.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>At this size, I can feel how thick
and strong her muscles are just by hanging
onto her leg.
Demon_Blush
\nr<Est>Hey, you pervert. Don't gawk over your enemy's legs.
Are you a muscle fetishist?
AlainFace
\n<Alain>I mean, as an adventurer, I just have
to compliment a well built body. It means
she's trained a lot.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Unfortunately, there's no sign of any
trap controlling magic tool here. I guess
we'll have to move on.
\v[18]/7 notes made on Wolf Beastkin.
A
AlainFace
\n<Alain>*cough* *cough* As expected of a physical
fighter. All that movement she's done going
up against Gale built up a lot of sweat.
Demon_Sad
\nr<Est>I'm glad I don't have to smell anything through
this dummy. The air's so thick from the heat her foot's
generating that it's actually hard to move.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Yeah. What are these things called?
Stirrups? They gave a lot of room for her
feet to breathe, but the stench still built
up somehow.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Unfortunately, these don't seem to be
a magic tool. Let's keep going.
\v[18]/7 notes made on Wolf Beastkin.
A
HP and SP were fully recovered!
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Okay. I made it through those crystals
unnoticed.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>While she's waiting for Gale to make a
move, I should try to find her weakness
or some way to deactivate whatever trap
she has waiting for Gale.
\n<????>Wait. if you're going to do that, let me help
you too.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>A voice? Who's there?
\nr<????>Forgot my voice already? Well, I guess you haven't
ever heard of it on your scale. Give me a moment. It'll
be easier once my talisman has an actual mouth.
MC2
MC2
Demon_Default
\nr<Demon>There. It's better to be able to talk to a physical
being than a disembodied voice, right?
The Demon Talisman has become an actual demon!
AlainFace
\n<Alain>What the-?! You! How did you get here?
Demon_Happy
\nr<Demon>Surprised? I gave you a talisman for a reason. That
thing is my connection to the world outside the hidden
village of elves.
\nr<Demon>I'm still hiding there. What you're talking to is
a dummy I'm controlling from a distance with magic.
Demon_Angry
\nr<Demon>Also, don't call me 'you'. I have a name. Since
we're working together, you may know it. It's Est.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>I've heard of puppetry magic to control
dolls from a distance, but to make a mirror
image of yourself from a talisman and to
control it... Demons sure are something.
Demon_Smug
\nr<Est>Heh. That's right. Praise me more. Making a dummy
your puny size is really convenient too because it
conserves a lot of mana.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>You sure are talkative. You were making
such a fuss about being low on mana when
we met before.
Demon_Angry
\nr<Est>You're the reason I used up more mana than I
wanted to!
Demon_Lecture
\nr<Est>But yes. I spoke to the Elf Village's Chief after
you left. She highly recommended adventurers from Niim
Town's guild.
\nr<Est>She assured me that I didn't have to hide if
you were somebody your Guild Master trusted.
\nr<Est>She also let me rest in the communal home. Let me
tell you: soft beds beat stone pedestals any day of the
week. My mana's recovering a lot more quickly now too.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Heh. Sounds you're doing good, then.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>And while I'm sure the village chief
has a bit of a bias, she's right. Gale and
I can get any job done!
Demon_Sad
\nr<Est>That overconfidence is disturbing when your dragon's
doing the heavy lifting and you're just crawling all
over people like a bug. Are you THAT excited about
crawling around a woman's body?
Demon_Blush
\nr<Est>After having experienced that firsthand, I'd crush
you like a grape if I didn't need you.
Demon_Angry
\nr<Est>Wait. Let me rephrase that. I'm going to crush you
for embarrassing me after I use you.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>I don't think you had to rephrase what
you just said there.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>And aren't you holding too much of
a grudge? I didn't do much.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>And you're a succubus. Was me walking all
over you last time really something to get
embarrassed about? I would've thought you'd
have experienced more degenerate things.
Demon_Blush
\nr<Est>Just because I'm a succubus doesn't mean that I
like to be violated! My fetishes are incredibly vanilla.
Demon_Shocked
Em_Shock
\nr<Est>A-Ah! I didn't mean it that way.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>You sure are a friendly succubus, Est.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>I'm sorry that we got off on the wrong
foot. It was just for a quest. No hard
feelings.
\nr<Est>Are you seriously dismissing what you and your
dragon did to me earlier? Are all of you adventurers
this nonchalant?
Demon_Lecture
\nr<Est>Ah. Whatever. Should we really be having this
conversation here at such a time and place?
Demon_Angry
\nr<Est>Taking care of this beastkin girl is our main goal
here. I refuse to let you mess this up when my life's
on the line too.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Sorry. Fine. Let's take this seriously.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>If you have any way to help, I'm willing to
listen. This wolf's dangerous.
Demon_Default
\nr<Est>Your goal is to either find a weakness or to
deactivate the trap, right? I can tell you right now
that finding a weakness is stupid.
\nr<Est>You can't do anything at your size against her
so \c[2]even if you uncover her weakness, you can't take
advantage of it. Your dragon is the only one who
could do anything on that level.\c[0]
Demon_Happy
\nr<Est>Thankfully, your other goal is more reasonable. This
part of the cavern you're in doesn't seem to be a part
of the main dungeon. That means the traps here have to
have been set up manually.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>This is a fake dungeon branch? So
Gale and I ended up wandering off the
main route the first time we were here?
AlainFace
\n<Alain>No wonder there were so many traps.
Whatever they were doing here, they didn't
want us to get any closer.
Demon_Default
\nr<Est>She doesn't seem to be a magic user, so that
means she has to have some magic tool that links to
the traps so she can engage and disengage them.
\nr<Est>If you find out where that magic tool is, then
I can deactivate it.
\nr<Est>This copy of mine is as mana sensitive as I am,
but because it's your size right now, we'll still have
to be pretty close to the magic tool to find it.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Hm... So you want me to give up on
finding weakness and just focus on finding
the magic tool? That makes sense.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Gale can get closer once the trap is
unusable and that will give her the
opportunity.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>Okay. Sounds like a plan, Est. I'm
counting on you from here on out.
Demon_Blush
\nr<Est>D-Don't be mistaken. This is only until there's
no longer the threat of someone trying to kill me.
Demon_Lecture
\nr<Est>Also, don't expect me to keep this replica of me
out all of the time. I need to conserve mana for one
thing, but I also don't want to get it involved in
any stupid or perverted antics of yours.
AlainFace
\n<Alain>I don't think I've done anything that
perverted...
The Succubus Demon, Est's, Talisman Dummy has joined
your party!
A
